chosen;
they only deal with the reactive bit at the bottom of the band, so subs
and bass
and midranges work out OK.

T&amp;S made it easy for bean counters to make boxes small and to design
drivers to fit them
so they could say they offered fine bass extension from a little box.

In fact what we got from makers was a bunch of over bean countered crap,
including silly things like AR12 with no ports, because when you tried
to fit one
it made no difference.
