ignored
and their designs dumbed down.

I once compared a Sonus Faber 2 way Concerto bookshelf to my own floor
stander
3 ways which have the extra octave of low bass and found the Sonus F
were
pretty fine speakers with good bass but they wouldn't go real low.
and once you turned up the wick they became quite muddled compared to my
3 way.
Probably because the FB is quite high, and not below 50Hz where it
should be.
But they are good bookshelfs, no doubt, and the guy who designed them
must have got his T&amp;S
parameters right IMHO.

Once the box matching gets to be too critical in ported enclosures,
bass suffers.

Many drivers are one heck of a lot better now than they were in 1972,
although the trend is now to cheap generic crap made in China
with very poor design and wide tolerances.

Human nature continues to cheat ppl of their hard earned cash.

