Exactly, which is why I said "sealed boxes", which are not 4h order and do
not have 2 resonant Q's.

My point was that a good large sealed enclosure design of the day, can still
beat the majority of small vented modern speakers in the lower octaves, AND
that the higher octaves are not goverened by the box design anyway. A lot
more speakers were three way 30 years ago, and the mid range and treble were
definitly not affected by vent size! (maybe in a non sealed mid range
without a proper enclosure)
What has really changed is preference for small box sizes and the ability to
provide much better performance in those sizes. The two obviously go hand in
hand.

My other point was that mid range and tweeter driver design and measurement
capability has had just as big an impact on sound quality IMO. The assertion
that T-S box design is the only, or even main factor in increased speaker
performance is just plain wrong, and I imagine you would agree?

